Fuji king Wasiu Ayinde Omogbolahan Marshall aka K1 has revealed plans to hold a colloquium in honour of his late mentor and Fuji legend, Sikiru Ayinde Agbajelola aka Barrister. The Maiyegun of Yoruba land made this known in a recent post shared on his official Instagram page.   Sammie Okposo apologises for fling with American lady, seeks…     Olakira bags Maserati automobile endorsement     Ex-wife of Mercy Aigbe’s new boo speaks up   While K1 refused to give more details about the event, he hinted that the colloquium is scheduled to be an annual event with activities such as lectures, tributes, and musical concerts embedded in the day. The musician, who also doubles as a hotelier, The Nation gathered, is bankrolling the event all by himself. The media consultant to the Fuji king, Kunle Rasheed, confirmed the event saying more details will be revealed in due time.